Diversified digital technology group Etion's loss widened in its year to end-March, as it moved to adapt its business to changing market conditions. The group saw R64m in one-off costs in the period, which exceeds its market capitalisation, as it wrote down inventory and retrenched staff amid a reorganisation of its businesses. The group reported an after tax loss of R36.1m, from a loss of R2.7m previously, also reporting an economically driven decline in demand for fibre connections to home and offices. The group provides network infrastructure and cybersecurity services. gernetzkyk@businesslive.co.za